scroll: core-distill-test
description: "Test for distill primitive - reduce content with intensity control"

requires:
  input_text:
    type: string
    description: "Text to distill"
    default: |
      Software development best practices encompass a wide range of methodologies and techniques
      that help teams deliver high-quality code efficiently. Test-driven development (TDD) is one
      such approach where developers write tests before implementing features, ensuring that code
      meets requirements from the start. Code reviews are another critical practice, allowing team
      members to catch bugs early and share knowledge across the team. Continuous integration and
      continuous deployment (CI/CD) pipelines automate the building, testing, and deployment of
      applications, reducing manual errors and speeding up release cycles. Documentation, while
      often overlooked, plays a vital role in maintaining codebases over time, helping new team
      members understand existing systems and reducing the cognitive load on experienced developers.
      Clean code principles, such as meaningful variable names, small functions, and single
      responsibility, make code more readable and maintainable for future development efforts.

steps:
  - distill:
      input: ${input_text}
      intensity: aggressive
      output_contract:
        length: sentence
        format: prose
    output: distilled_result
